<h2><b>5. INFORMATION RELATING TO CHILDREN</b></h2>
6.1 We do not knowingly collect or solicit Personal Information from children under the age of majority or knowingly allow children under the age of majority to register for the InHotel Service. If you are under the age of majority, do not register or attempt to register for any of the InHotel Service or send any information about yourself to us. No one under the age of majority may provide any Personal Information to, on or through the InHotel Service.<br/>
6.2 If we learn that we have collected or been sent Personal Information from a child under the age of majority, we will delete that Personal Information as soon as reasonably practical. If you believe that we might have collected or been sent Personal Information from a child under the age of majority, please contact our Support team.
<h2><b>6. DATA WE COLLECT OTHER THAN PERSONAL INFORMATION</b></h2>
7.1 In addition to Personal Information, we collect data on your use and interaction with the InHotel Service. Data which we obtain about you, other than Personal Information, is the exclusive property of  InHotel and may be used by InHotel in any manner permitted by applicable laws.
<h2><b>7. RETENTION OF PERSONAL INFORMATION AND OTHER DATA</b></h2>
7.1 InHotel reserves the right to retain your Personal Information, other data collected about you and content you submit to or through the InHotel Service to the extent required by applicable laws, rules and regulations and as reasonably necessary to protect our legal interests and operate our business.
<h2><b>8. DATA TRANSMISSION AND STORAGE</b></h2>
9.1 No data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Consequently, we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us and you do so at your own risk.<br/>
9.2 InHotel may use third party vendors and/or hosting partners to provide the necessary hardware, software, networking, storage, and related technology required to run the InHotel Service. Where practical, we seek to obtain confidentiality agreements that are consistent with this Privacy Policy and that limit others&acute; use or disclosure of your Personal Information.<br/>
<h2><b>9. INTERNATIONAL USE</b></h2>
19.1 The InHotel Service is hosted in by Namecheap in the United States. If you use the InHotel Service from outside of the United States, you acknowledge that you are voluntarily transferring information (potentially including Personal Information) to the United States and agree that InHotels&acute;s collection, use, storage and sharing of your information is exclusively subject to the laws of the United States, not of the jurisdiction in which you are located. Under some circumstances, the laws of UK may apply as InHotel is incorporated in UK.<br/>
<h2><b>11. QUESTIONS</b></h2>
11. Any questions about this Privacy Policy should be addressed to <b>info@inhotel-app.com</b>

